    "7 further visualizes how varying the number of branches and initialization methods (random vs. constant) affects model performance across four key metrics-accuracy, specificity, sensitivity, and AUC.",
    "Each subplot corresponds to one performance metric, clearly illustrating that configurations with two or three branches achieve the best balance across all metrics, while performance begins to decline with four or more branches."
